citations:
    citation-agot-sansa-iv:
        source: source-agot
        properties:
            locator: "Sansa IV"
            text_from_source: "Your father is a traitor, dear … We found this on the captain of your household guard, Sansa. It is a letter to my late husband's brother Stannis, inviting him to take the crown."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "Sansa is held in Maegor's Holdfast with Jeyne Poole for three days after the coup. She is brought before Cersei and the small council. Cersei accuses Ned of treason. Sansa writes letters to Lady Catelyn, Robb, Lysa Arryn, and Lord Hoster Tully urging them to keep the king's peace. Jeyne Poole is removed to Littlefinger's custody. Sansa hears Robert's death bells on the second day."
